  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "Okay, here's a breakdown of how you typically pay installments with Krazybee, along with important things to keep in mind:\n\n**Typical Payment Methods**\n\nKrazybee usually offers a variety of convenient payment options to pay your installments. Here are the most common ones:\n\n*   **UPI (Unified Payments Interface):** This is likely the most common and convenient method. You can use apps like PhonePe, Google Pay, Paytm, BHIM, etc., to pay directly from your bank account. Krazybee will usually provide a UPI ID or a QR code for you to scan and pay.\n\n*   **Debit Card:** Pay using your debit card.\n\n*   **Net Banking:** Transfer funds directly from your bank account through net banking.\n\n*   **Wallets:** Some digital wallets might be accepted. Check the app for supported wallets.\n\n**Steps to Pay Your Installments**\n\nHere's a general guide on how to make your installment payments:\n\n1.  **Open the Krazybee App:**  This is the primary way you'll manage your account and payments.\n\n2.  **Log In:** Use your registered mobile number and password to log in.\n\n3.  **Go to \"My Orders\" or \"My Loans\":**  Look for a section in the app that shows your active purchases or loans. The wording might vary slightly.\n\n4.  **Select the Relevant Order/Loan:**  Choose the specific purchase for which you want to pay the installment.\n\n5.  **View Installment Details:**  You should see a breakdown of your installment schedule, including the due date, installment amount, and any late payment fees (if applicable).\n\n6.  **Choose Payment Method:** Select your preferred payment method from the options available (UPI, Debit Card, Net Banking, etc.).\n\n7.  **Follow Payment Instructions:**\n    *   **UPI:** If you choose UPI, you'll likely see a UPI ID or a QR code. Open your UPI app (e.g., PhonePe, Google Pay), enter the UPI ID, or scan the QR code.  Enter the correct installment amount and complete the payment.\n    *   **Debit Card/Net Banking:** You'll be redirected to a secure payment gateway. Enter your card details or net banking credentials and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the payment.\n\n8.  **Confirmation:** After successful payment, you should receive a confirmation message within the Krazybee app and possibly via SMS/email. Keep a screenshot or record of your payment confirmation for your records.\n\n**Important Things to Remember**\n\n*   **Due Dates:**  Pay close attention to your installment due dates. Late payments usually incur penalties, which can increase the overall cost of your purchase.\n*   **Installment Amount:** Always double-check that you are paying the correct installment amount.\n*   **Payment Confirmation:** Always ensure you receive a payment confirmation after making the payment. If you don't, contact Krazybee customer support immediately.\n*   **App Notifications:**  Enable notifications from the Krazybee app. They often send reminders about upcoming installments.\n*   **Customer Support:**  If you have any problems or questions about your payments, don't hesitate to contact Krazybee's customer support. You can usually find contact information (phone number, email) within the app or on their website.\n\n**Troubleshooting Common Issues**\n\n*   **Payment Failed:** If your payment fails, try again with a different payment method or check your bank account balance.\n*   **Payment Not Reflected:** If you made a payment but it's not showing up in the app, wait a few hours (sometimes it takes a little time to process). If it's still not reflected after 24 hours, contact Krazybee customer support with your payment proof.\n*   **Login Issues:** If you can't log in, try resetting your password. If that doesn't work, contact customer support.\n\n**Disclaimer:**\n*The information provided here is a general guide based on common practices for online installment payment platforms like Krazybee. The specific payment methods, steps, and app interface may vary slightly. Always refer to the official Krazybee app or website for the most accurate and up-to-date information.*",
